cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the study of games from a mathematical perspective, which is closely related to game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The development of mathematical formalism and equivalence relations also suggests a focus on discrete structures (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM). Finally, the exploration of gameplay phenomena and player behavior may also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
